    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1456"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/152.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have just received telegram from Díaz Lombardo at Chihuahua repeating message he
                    received from Guadalajara relative Jalisco State tax on foreigners as follows:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Nothing definite has been decided owing to absence of Governor but no
                            energetic measures have been taken against any one. I will keep you
                            informed.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This means that matter is still held in abeyance and I am sure that no action
                    will be taken to enforce payment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
